Marseille <- read_table("/Users/shalliday/Google Drive/simondhalliday.github.io/bfh-textbook/indmarketdemand/MARS.txt", col_names = FALSE)
head(Marseille)
## Source: local data frame [6 x 8]
## 
##      X1    X2                 X3     X4    X5    X6    X7    X8
##   (int) (int)              (chr)  (int) (int) (int) (int) (int)
## 1     2 18064 ESCALE BASTIA 1002 880105  5415    77   110  4000
## 2     2 18070 ESCALE BASTIA 1002 880105  5415    44   120  2200
## 3     2 18078 PSS DE L'OPERA1002 880104  5505   214    90  6500
## 4     2 18081 GENTY PERTUIS 1002 880105 10080   214   150  6500
## 5     2 18085 MONTLAUR      1002 880102 10090    77   205  3600
## 6     2 18088 MONTLAUR      1002 880102 10090    44    60  1800
Marseille <- 
  Marseille %>%
  rename(sellerb = X1, lot = X2, nbuyer = X3, date = X4, buyerc = X5, fish = X6, tempa = X7, tempb = X8) 
Mars <- 
  Marseille %>%
  mutate(weight = tempa/10, price = tempb/100)
head(Mars)
## Source: local data frame [6 x 10]
## 
##   sellerb   lot             nbuyer   date buyerc  fish tempa tempb weight
##     (int) (int)              (chr)  (int)  (int) (int) (int) (int)  (dbl)
## 1       2 18064 ESCALE BASTIA 1002 880105   5415    77   110  4000   11.0
## 2       2 18070 ESCALE BASTIA 1002 880105   5415    44   120  2200   12.0

## 6       2 18088 MONTLAUR      1002 880102  10090    44    60  1800    6.0
## Variables not shown: price (dbl)
Mars %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = weight, y = price)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  stat_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y ~ x, size = 1) +
  ylim(0, 100)
